{"key":"processedPost-6871887","value":{"id":6871887,"first":6871460,"last":6872535,"when":1178298631,"utime":"05/04/07 08:10 PM","content":"I've seen them go MUCH longer than that.  It's not recommended, but people have left cakes submerged in the refrigerator for weeks without killing the mycelium. In fact, I have liquid mycelium cultures stored in the refrigerator for years that are still viable.<br /><br />However, 24 to 36 hours is the recommended time for dunking cakes, and bulk substrates are usually fully hydrated after 4 to 6 hours.  The biggest reason for not going longer than that is bacteria will grow from the substrate in the anaerobic conditions under water.<br />RR","title":"Re: cake left helpless","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}